# Domain Functions

## Create Sub Domains

- Log on to cPanel Interface of your website.
- Click on Subdomains under Domains.

```diagram

```

- In drop down window select the domain that you want to add the sub domain for
- In the box before the domain enter the name of the subdomain that you want to add

```diagram

```

- Now click on Document root box and it should populate the values
- Then hit enter or click Create button

## Redirection on Subdomain

**Add Redirection**

- Log on to cPanel Interface of your website.
- Click on Subdomains under Domains.

```diagram

```

- You should see a list of subdomains, scroll down, under actions click on  Manage Redirection

```diagram

```

- Put the target domain name in the text box and save it

```diagram

```


**Remove Redirection**


- Log on to cPanel Interface of your website.
- Click on Subdomains under Domains.
- You should see a list of subdomains, scroll down. Select the domain and under actions click on Manage Redirection
- Click on Disable Button to remove redirection

```diagram

```


## Delete Subdomains

- Login to cPanel and click on Subdomains
- You should see a list of subdomains, scroll down. Select the domain and under actions click on remove to remove subdomain

```diagram

```


## Create Addon Domain

An addon domain is a separate domain that is hosted on your primary domain but it appears as if it is hosted on it's own account. To use the addon domains feature , you must have a registered domain name and it should be using the name servers as your primary domain is using.
- 
- Login to cPanel of your website
- Under Domains click on Addon Domains

```diagram

```

- Now you should see a form asking for domain name, username, document root directory and password fields.
- 
- Enter the domain name and it will populate the directory name.
- Mention the password in password field.

```diagram

```

- Then click on Add Domain button

## Remove Addon Domains

- Login to cPanel of your website
- Under Domains click on Addon Domains

```diagram

```

- You should see the list of addon domains that are added.
- Find the remove option next to addon domain that you want to remove, click on it and the domain will be deleted.


## Add Park Domain

> A parked domain is a domain name that points to your main domain or primary domain.
> 
> If myweb.net is your main Web site, you can purchase the myweb.com and assign it as a parked domain so that if a visitor were to type myweb.com they would see the same Web site as if they had typed myweb.net.
> 
> A parked domain should be a registered domain.
{.is-info}


- Log on to cPanel of your Website
- Under Domains click on Parked Domain

```diagram

```

- In the New Domain Name box, provide the domain name for which you would like to park on top of your primary domain.

```diagram

```

- Then click on Add Domain

## Setup Redirect for Websites

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Under Domains click on Redirects

```diagram

```

- Keep the setting of 301 as it is
- From the drop down window select the domain for which you want to set the redirect.
- In the next field enter an optional path and file name
- Then enter the full URL of the website for the redirect target
- Keep other settings as it is

```diagram

```

- Click on the Add button and you are done

## How to Disable Redirection 

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Under Domains click on Redirects

```diagram

```


- You should now see the existing redirects for your website

```diagram

```

- Click on the  CROSS icon near to the redirection in order to disable it.

## Enabling hotlink protection

Hotlinking protection option in cpanel protects your website from linking to files and images on your website 

Steps:

- To access Hotlink Protection, click on the icon above the words Hotlink Protection on the main screen of your cPanel interface.

```diagram

```

- Click on "Enable" to enable protection.
- Now in "URLs to allow access" box  make sure the domain name is there for which you want to enable Hotlinking protection.
- In the box which says "Block direct access for these extensions", provide the extensions for which you would like to block.

```diagram

```

- Now Skip the "Redirect request to this URL" box and click Submit button.

##  Add A/CNAME record to website DNS zone file

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Under Domains click on Simple DNS Zone Editor

```diagram

```

- To add new A record, write your domain name under Name filed and put your IP address in Address filed.

```diagram

```

- Then click on Add a Record button and you are done
- 
- To add a new CNAME record, write your domain name under Name filed and put your domain name in CNAME filed.

```diagram

```


- Then click on Add CNAME Record button and you are done
- Then below you can see current records you already created. 
- You can view all current records you created. If you want delete any of them, then simply click on Delete under Action

```diagram

```
